            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-question-text">Will this include credentials or sensitive values?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                Relay uses only what exists in the export and is designed to produce <strong>safe-to-share</strong> documentation.
                (Still: review before sending externally, as you would with any export.)
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-question-text">Can I run both reports from the same export?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                Yes — that’s the whole point: one export generates either report. Many teams run the free Audit first, then generate the Continuity Report for the final handoff bundle.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-10 text-center">
